-- int_deduped_channels.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate customer_channels to primary attribution (earliest per customer)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        attributed_at,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_revenue_by_channel_city.sql
```sql
-- Calculate customer revenue by attribution channel and store city
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        c.customer_id,
        COALESCE(ch.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel,
        COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city,
        t.amount
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_customers') }} c
        ON c.customer_id = t.customer_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_channels') }} ch
        ON ch.customer_id = t.customer_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_stores') }} s
        ON s.store_id = t.store_id
)
SELECT
    channel,
    city,
    SUM(amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(*) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM source
GROUP BY
    channel,
    city
ORDER BY
    total_revenue DESC
